{"task":"transcribe","language":"english","duration":30.0,"text":"The middle and late pre-classic farmers of the southern lowlands were undeniably successful, for their archaeological record reveals a continuously rising population. Webster suggests that there was population pressure in the Pecan region by about 500 BC, while N. Hammond concludes that by the late pre-classic, population density and site spacing were such that any further growth would have led to competition. Based on their research in the central Petain Lakes region, D.V. et al.","segments":[{"id":0,"seek":0,"start":1.0800000429153442,"end":6.0,"text":" The middle and late pre-classic farmers of the southern lowlands were undeniably successful,","tokens":[50364,440,2808,293,3469,659,12,11665,299,11339,295,264,13456,2295,10230,645,674,15711,1188,4406,11,50696],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2769731283187866,"compression_ratio":1.6007752418518066,"no_speech_prob":0.014276720583438873},{"id":1,"seek":0,"start":6.619999885559082,"end":10.180000305175781,"text":" for their archaeological record reveals a continuously rising population.","tokens":[50696,337,641,42139,2136,20893,257,15684,11636,4415,13,50938],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2769731283187866,"compression_ratio":1.6007752418518066,"no_speech_prob":0.014276720583438873},{"id":2,"seek":0,"start":11.460000038146973,"end":15.880000114440918,"text":" Webster suggests that there was population pressure in the Pecan region by about 500","tokens":[50938,9573,3120,13409,300,456,390,4415,3321,294,264,2396,7035,4458,538,466,5923,51174],"temperature":0.0,"avg_logprob":-0.2769731283187866,"compression_ratio":1.6007752418518066,"no_speech_prob":0.014276720583438873},{"id":3,"seek":0,"start":16.200000762939453,"end":21.81999969482422,"text":" BC, while N. Hammond concludes that by the late pre-classic, population density and site","tokens":[51174,14359,11,1339,426,13,34842,684,24643,300,538,264,3469,659,12,11665,299,11,4415,10305,293,3621,51451],"te